Two affiliated investment firms andfunds they control told the Securities and Exchange Commissionthey raised their Orient Express Hotels Inc stake to 1,663,800shares, or 17.0 pct of the total, from 1,560,800, or 15.9 pct.    The firms, Boston-based FMR Corp and Bermuda-based FidelityInternational Ltd, said they bought a combined 103,000 OrientExpress common shares from March 12 to April 8 at pricesranging from 3.05 to 3.55 dlrs each. Reuter&#3;